{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-9ab074b4e61f",
  "content": "## Design\n\n### Fix 1: Cargo.toml Module Tree Resolution (D72)\n\n**Crate:** `corvia-adapter-git`\n\n**Approach:** Parse `Cargo.toml` to find crate roots, scan `.rs` files for `mod foo;` declarations to build a full module→file map, then use this map in `resolve_rust_module_path()`.\n\n**New components:**\n\n- **`RustModuleMap`** — struct that maps module paths to file paths\n  - Built by parsing `Cargo.toml` (find `[lib]`/`[[bin]]` entries, default to `src/lib.rs` or `src/main.rs`)\n  - Walks each crate root scanning for `mod foo;` declarations (not inline `mod foo { }`)\n  - Resolves `mod foo;` to `foo.rs` or `foo/mod.rs` by checking the file system\n  - Handles workspace `Cargo.toml` with `[workspace] members` to discover all crates\n\n- **`resolve_rust_module_path()` changes:**\n  - Takes `Option<&RustModuleMap>` parameter\n  - For `crate::config`, looks up the map → returns resolved file path (e.g., `crates/corvia-common/src/config.rs`)\n  - For `super::foo`, resolves relative to current file's parent module\n  - Falls back to current behavior if map is unavailable or path not found\n\n- **Integration:**\n  - `GitAdapter::register_chunking()` builds the `RustModuleMap` from the workspace root\n  - Stores the map in `AstChunker` via `set_module_map(map)`\n  - `AstChunker::chunk()` passes the map through to treesitter relation extraction\n\n**Expected yield:** ~38 existing import relations become real cross-file edges. Cross-crate imports within the workspace (e.g., `corvia_common::config`) may also become resolvable if the workspace `Cargo.toml` is parsed.\n\n**Alternatives rejected:**\n- (A) File-system-aware resolution without Cargo.toml — simpler but can't resolve module paths correctly without knowing crate roots\n- (C) Post-hoc matching in `wire_pipeline_relations()` — messier, doesn't fix the adapter's output\n\n---\n",
